## Asset cells:
An asset cell is split in three sections: left, mid, right section. left and right sections can be collapsed by user.
### left section: contains list of labled values with units (quantities) like: 
- current power [kW] (sign determines direction), 
- current cost rate [€/h]
- current GHG rate [GHGEQ/h] (GHGEQ stands for any unit to measure kg CO2 equivalents, replace it if you have a better unit)
- forcast Energy in visible graph (Sum of all forcasted/planned/requested energy slices that are visible. check wheter this values are available on the UI api, else drop it)
- if available: the timely closest or currently active, largest (if more than one active) user request for that asset with due time and requested energy.

### mid section: diagram with multiple graphs 
- x axis is time with past time on the left half, present in the middle and future on the right half.
- the present is marked with a vertical red doted line
- y axis is for multiple scales (unclear how much is possible, maybe no scale at all and just add units in the legend?)
    - graph for Power [kW], past, present, future (forecast/planned). normal line type
    - graph for cost rate [€/h], dashed line type
    - graph for GHG rate [GHGEQ/h], dotted line type
- (maybe stating the obvious:) values have signs therefore the graphs can be above or below the x axis
- each asset has a separate color, all graphs in one asset cell have the same color, they are distinct by their line type.

### right section: changeable sliders and on/off buttons to influence the value of the asset simulator
upper half of the section: status setting, e.g. 
 - SoC (user can change SoC any time enven though simulated energy flow also changes it), 
 - power on/off (user can simulate with that a EV plugged in state, a asset switched on or off by user etc.)
lower half of the section: simulation chatacteristics override, e.g. 
 - battery capacity, 
 - power limits, delays etc.

It is yet unclear to me how much space those controls will take in the right section. it might get crowded. suggest solutions if there are.

## Grid cells:
there are two grid cells: one for tariffs and one for accumulated asset power. grid cells have only two sections, left for values and right for diagram, grid cannot be manipulated by VEN, therefore no controlls to influence.
### tariff cell:
left section: 
- current import tariff [€/kWh]
- current import tariff [GHG rate [GHGEQ/h]
- current export tariff [€/kWh]
- current total cost rate [€/h]
- current grid power [kW]
right section: graph of past, present, future (same style as asset graphs) 
- import tariff [€/kWh] (red dashed)
- import tariff [GHG rate [GHGEQ/h] (ret dotted)
- export tariff [€/kWh] (green dashed)
- total cost rate [€/h] (black dashed)
- grid power [kW] (black normal)

### accumulated asset power cell: showing summary of asset power
left section: list of all assets current power in [kW]

right section: graph of past, present, future (same style as asset graphs) 
this graph is special. it shall be a graph of colored areas stacked on each other (like sediments of a geological cut view)
positive values gets added above the x axis, negative values gets added below the x axis. (all values added together should be equal to the current grid power at any time.)

